The paper deals with matrix completion and approximation, which are common problems in machine learning and data science. The approach taken in the paper is based on an additive model of co-clusterings, which is a novel technique for matrix approximation. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category is the most likely because the paper deals with a machine learning problem (matrix completion and approximation) and proposes a new approach based on a novel model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category is also likely because matrix completion and approximation are important problems in information retrieval, especially in recommender systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category is relevant because the paper proposes an iterative minimization algorithm and a collapsed Gibbs sampler for the proposed model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category is relevant because the paper deals with a problem that is important in AI (matrix completion and approximation) and proposes a new approach based on a novel model. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category is relevant because matrix completion and approximation are important problems in network analysis, especially in link prediction and recommendation.
